                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14470366" author="pniederw" created="Fri, 15 Oct 2010 09:52:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In a sense, the behavior is more consistent now, because you always need a separator. In 1.7 you could get by without a separator in some cases (*1) but not in others (*2).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(*1) &lt;tt&gt;if (true) x += 2 else false // works in 1.7 but not in 1.8&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(*2) &lt;tt&gt;if (true) x else false // works neither in 1.7 nor in 1.8; either need to wrap x with braces, or add a semicolon after it&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally, neither example would need a separator, similar to statements like &lt;tt&gt;if (true) println 1 else println 2&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471003" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 8 Mar 2011 09:13:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
